      },
      "snippet": "I ordered a seasonal latte. 8 bucks, one of the highest prices in the city. it was foamy. if you know anything about lattes, foamy is not how the milk should be steamed. that\u2019s a cappuccino. not to mention, their seasonal syrup is really mediocre. the staff is nice though!\n\nI emailed them about my experience weeks ago. no response. they seem to not care about their customer experience anymore, probably since they\u2019ve been bought out by a big corporate.\n\ncheck out third wheel coffee a few blocks away, they pull some of the best shots within a mile radius. skip blue bottle. trust me.",
      "extracted_snippet": {
        "original": "I ordered a seasonal latte. 8 bucks, one of the highest prices in the city. it was foamy. if you know anything about lattes, foamy is not how the milk should be steamed. that\u2019s a cappuccino. not to mention, their seasonal syrup is really mediocre. the staff is nice though!\n\nI emailed them about my experience weeks ago. no response. they seem to not care about their customer experience anymore, probably since they\u2019ve been bought out by a big corporate.\n\ncheck out third wheel coffee a few blocks away, they pull some of the best shots within a mile radius. skip blue bottle. trust me."
      },
