        "local_guide": true,
        "reviews": 1,
        "photos": 0
      },
      "snippet": "I stopped by Blue Bottle while walking through Hayes Valley, and it honestly turned into one of the highlights of my afternoon. The space feels bright and minimal, but still warm and welcoming. My cappuccino was smooth with just the right amount of foam, and you can really taste the quality of the beans. The staff moved quickly but never made me feel rushed. I ended up sitting by the window longer than I planned, just enjoying the calm atmosphere and watching the neighborhood go by.",
      "extracted_snippet": {
        "original": "I stopped by Blue Bottle while walking through Hayes Valley, and it honestly turned into one of the highlights of my afternoon. The space feels bright and minimal, but still warm and welcoming. My cappuccino was smooth with just the right amount of foam, and you can really taste the quality of the beans. The staff moved quickly but never made me feel rushed. I ended up sitting by the window longer than I planned, just enjoying the calm atmosphere and watching the neighborhood go by."
      },
